Spring Batch 2.0.2.RELEASE Release Notes


* Sub-task

  *{{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1327}[BATCH-1327]}} -         Prevent re-processing and re-writing on rollback after non-skippable and non-retryable exception

  * {{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1331}[BATCH-1331]}} -         Fatal exceptions that are also marked as no-rollback

  * {{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1332}[BATCH-1332]}} -         Skippable exceptions on write that are also marked as no-rollback cause a rollback, and double processing of item (writer and skip listener)

  * {{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1333}[BATCH-1333]}} -         Support for retry of non-skippable subclasses of skippable exceptions

  * {{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1334}[BATCH-1334]}} -         Exception marked as no-rollback but not skippable should not cause skips

  * {{{https://jira.spring.io/browse/BATCH-1335}[BATCH-1335]}} -         Pathological cases of no-rollback-for-exceptions on framework panic exceptions


    
